        <string>aod.npc_kleitos_met = true;</string>
        <string>useCameraBookmark(NPC_Kleitos_cam_01);</string>
        <string>dlgTeleportToMarker(TM_DLG_Kleitos);</string>
        <string>dlgRotateToChar(1105);</string>
      </onLoadScripts>
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>"I need a few things."</text>
          <def_link>2120</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>2119</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>"Of course you do. Who doesn't, eh? By the way, I've just got some nice crossbows from Maadoran. You don't strike me as a "look ‘em in the eyes while you gut them" kinda &lt;guy/gal&gt;, so if you like to keep your distance, look no further.

"Let me show you the different models..."</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>Listen to the sales pitch.</text>
          <def_link>2121</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>"Another time, Kleitos. Just show me what you have."</text>
          <def_link>2125</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>2120</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>"This little guy here," Kleitos shows you a small one-handed crossbow, "is nothing but a toy. Can't shoot straight and has no power, but I suppose you can't miss, if you shove it in someone's face, can you? You can hold it with one hand. Hell, you can hold two if you like, and I don't think I have to tell you what that means.

"Now this here is a real crossbow," he pulls out a basic model. "As standard as they come. Good, accurate, reliable. That's my number one choice. I fought two wars with it, and have nothing but good things to say about it. However, if you want something bigger and better, try its cousin over here. The difference? Feel it. Try to wind it. See how slowly it goes? It will take you longer to wind it for another shot, but the extra power is well worth the wait. It will punch a clean hole through any armor."</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>Continue.</text>
          <def_link>2122</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>2121</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>"Now, take a look at this," Kleitos shows you a double crossbow. "This strange-looking bird has two bows. They are vertical, of course, which is what makes the magic possible. You can shoot twice without reloading. Sweet little deal, eh?

"I saved the best for last," he puts a heavy bundle on the counter and carefully unwraps it. "A repeating crossbow! Is this a fucking marvel or what? I tell you, only the Zhin can come up with crazy shit like this. See this box on top? Load it up with bolts, aim, and fire. No, it's not fully automatic, although I've heard things you aint gonna believe... So, you still have to reload it after each shot, but it will only take a heartbeat or two. Obviously, it aint nearly as powerful as the heavy crossbow, but if speed is your thing, you can't go wrong with this one. If you've got the coin, that is. A *lot* of coin."</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>"Alright, show me the merchandise."</text>
          <def_link>2125</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>2122</UID>
    </dlgPart>
